        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 6:22AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 622 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 8 miles
northeast of Fanshawe, moving northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Bokoshe...                        Scullyville...
Shady Point...                    Panama...
Milton...                         Pocola...
Spiro...                          Cowlington...
Poteau...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
